			<div id = "comment-7499" class = "comment">
				<p>So the frequency of the PID controller does not have to be the same as of the frequency of sending PWM signal to the flight controller even if the frequency of the PWM signal is only at 50 Hz? What is the usual frequency for PID controller?</p>
			</div>
			<div id = "comment-7501" class = "comment">
				<p>There is no "usual" frequency for PID controls.  If you wanted to PID control the steering on a large boat, 1Hz might be fine; for some flying robots, you may want it to be much higher than 50Hz.  Higher frequency is generally better than lower frequency, but if your ESC can only accept 50 inputs per second then there's no gain to making your PID run faster than that.</p>
